if we want to slow our scan down we would use the -T option to specify one of these canned speeds
nmap -sT $ip -p 21,80 -T sneaky

nmap allows you to specify your scan delay speed using the --scan-delay option
nmap -sT $ip -p 21,80 --scan-delay 5s

we can also pass the speed argument in the form of milliseconds 
nmap -sT skillsetlocal.com -p 21,80 --scan-delay 5ms
